records.addlTxt:
Defendant Nicholas N. NOWIKOWSKI in court with attorney Kevin D. Musolf. Prosecuting Atty Angelina R Scarpelli appeared for State of Wisconsin.
Before going on the record today the Court went through the prior record of this case to see if he appeared on the case while he was employed in the DA office. He did appear on behalf of the State at the initial appearance on 09-15-2014. 
The parties do not object to the court proceeding today. 
Rights explained. 
Count 2  Deliver heroin as repeater  No contest plea entered. 
Convicted. 
The State moves to dismiss and read in count 1. Motion granted.
Parties comment.
Sentence withheld. Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for a period of four (4) years. Conditions of probation:
1)	Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
2)	AODA assessment and follow through;
3)	Maintain absolute sobriety;
4)	Submit to random urine screens and pay for the same;
5)	Maintain fulltime employment, schooling, job search, or combination;
6)	Spend twelve (12) months in the Manitowoc County Jail, under the Huber Law, commencing 02-18-2020 by 6:00 p.m.;
7)	Obtain an HSED or GED;
8)	Pay court costs;
9)	Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
10)	Submit to a DNA sample.
The court finds that the defendant has 19 days sentence credit if revoked. 
The Court allows the defense thirty (30) days to submit something in writing regarding credit. If the State agrees with the credit they can submit a stipulation. If there is no agreement the matter will be set for a hearing. 
The Court orders that the bail be returned to Melissa Reinl. 
The Court cautions the defendant that if the defendant has any law violations the jail time will commence immediately. 
The DA comments that if he does not report to jail they would be recommending prison. 
Minutes.
